<dl id="n12028d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12028d">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12028d"> 28(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Martin (Merlin)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">C&apos;est &agrave; eux &hellip; qu&apos;on doit demander l&apos;origine du personnage singulier appel&eacute; par les anciens Bretons, Marthin &hellip; et par les Fran&ccedil;ais, Merlin <br><font color="green">[It is to [the testimony of classical writers]</font> <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> that we must turn if we want to know the origin of the singular character that the ancient Bretons call <mark>Marthin</mark>; the modern Welsh Myrdhin; the Armoricans Marzin; the Scots Meller or Melziar, and the French <mark>Merlin</mark>] <small> [TLMM]Th&eacute;odore-Claude Hersart, Vicomte de La Villemarqu&eacute;, <cite a>Myrdhinn, ou l'enchanteur Merlin</cite></a> (1862) 3</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
